# exportedKeys

**Instance Property**

Returns an array of the exported keys.

## Declaration

```swift
var exportedKeys: [AnyHashable : Any] { get }
```

## Return Value

An array of dictionaries that describe the exported key and target object. See [doc://com.apple.coreimage/documentation/CoreImage/kCIFilterGeneratorExportedKey], [doc://com.apple.coreimage/documentation/CoreImage/kCIFilterGeneratorExportedKeyTargetObject],  and [doc://com.apple.coreimage/documentation/CoreImage/kCIFilterGeneratorExportedKey] for keys used in the dictionary.

## Discussion

This method returns the keys that you exported using the [doc://com.apple.coreimage/documentation/CoreImage/CIFilterGenerator/exportKey(_:from:withName:)] method or that were exported before being written to the file from which you read the filter chain.

## Managing Exported Keys

- **exportKey(_:from:withName:)**: Exports an input or output key of an object in the filter chain.
- **removeExportedKey(_:)**: Removes a key that was previously exported.
- **setAttributes(_:forExportedKey:)**: Sets a dictionary of attributes for an exported key.
